Jonnie Peacock of Team GB sprints for the finish line in the Men's T64 100m final at the 2020 Tokyo Paralympic Games. 

Peacock, a gold medallist in 2012 and 2016, shared the bronze medal with Germany's Johannes Floors after a photo finish judged them to have both remarkably clocked in at 10.786 seconds. 

#athletics #sport #disabilityinclusion #running #tokyo2020 

REUTERS/Molly Darlington
